⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⠀
In slide two, you’ll see someone’s comment on a post about taking outside stressors into consideration when coaching. I agreed with the post, but this asshat clearly didn’t. Instead, Man-Karen decided this was too PC and he wanted “science-based” interventions.⁠⠀
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⠀
I was furious - but I realized it goes deeper… Recently, I've seen lots of posts about calories or non-exercise activity being important for health… I agree, I also think we’re coming at this the wrong way...⁠⠀
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⠀
Food quantity and movement are important, many of these posts did a great job breaking down TDEE - they were well informed and well-intentioned. We’re operating under the assumption that our clients are able to just snap their fingers and start implementing lifestyle changes.⁠⠀
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⠀
Did that one click? Things don’t just “happen” after a little bit of education...⁠⠀
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⠀
We’re so stuck on the “what” that we miss the “who” - talking about what to do to be healthier, but not looking at WHO is on the other end.⁠⠀
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⠀
Ever felt like you had a lot on your plate? Life changes, bills, or an asshole boss… Stacked up on the deeper things that we don’t talk about.⁠⠀
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⠀
Feeling shame for how we look.⁠⠀
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⠀
Guilt for eating cookies.⁠⠀
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⠀
Childhood trauma.⁠⠀
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⠀
Access to healthy food, and our biological stress response.⁠⠀
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⠀
These are what makes it harder to choose between watching TV and going for a walk, even if we know the walk is better for us. Stress leads to fight, flight, or freeze. Not learning or trying something new. Our habits are what we do without thinking - our fallback for when stress happens and we need to focus on a perceived threat.⁠⠀
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⠀
We need to work on stress, first - then put the power into our client’s hands... What can they change? Are they able to change that thing right now? How will they change it?⁠⠀
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⠀
If we want to change behavior, we need to create a path to success WITH our client, USING science… Not a path that solely RELIES on science.⁠⠀
⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⠀
We take a human, look-at-the-big-picture approach.";}i:82;a:1:{s:14:"comments_count";i:1;}i:83;a:1:{s:11:"likes_count";i:3;}i:84;a:1:{s:4:"link";s:39:"https://www.instagram.com/p/CEu4hI8DJxK";}i:85;a:1:{s:5:"image";s:250:"https://scontent-sin6-2.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.2885-15/e35/s1080x1080/118681126_3755115754501652_6704703395689966108_n.jpg?_nc_ht=scontent-sin6-2.cdninstagram.com&_nc_cat=108&_nc_ohc=EqPyO8q_rywAX81JUf_&oh=83cc9c4df3dc59ac79091e62155da5c8&oe=5F7DEC59";}i:86;a:1:{s:4:"type";s:7:"sidecar";}i:87;a:1:{s:8:"owner_id";i:19861235;}i:88;a:1:{s:14:"owner_username";s:0:"";}i:89;a:1:{s:14:"owner_fullname";s:0:"";}i:90;a:1:{s:9:"owner_pic";s:0:"";}i:91;a:1:{s:2:"id";s:19:"2391096945902835690";}i:92;a:1:{s:10:"short_code";s:11:"CEu4gD0D1fq";}i:93;a:1:{s:12:"created_time";i:1599260989;}i:94;a:1:{s:7:"caption";s:219:"For those days when you need a bit of calm. This is a gentle blend of calming herbs brought together to assist with symptoms of stress and anxiety. Create a sense of harmony and inner peace with our Calm Me tea 🌱🍵";}i:95;a:1:{s:14:"comments_count";i:2;}i:96;a:1:{s:11:"likes_count";i:3;}i:97;a:1:{s:4:"link";s:39:"https://www.instagram.com/p/CEu4gD0D1fq";}i:98;a:1:{s:5:"image";s:249:"https://scontent-sin6-2.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.2885-15/e35/s1080x1080/118794384_184169706498641_7177768790430657574_n.jpg?_nc_ht=scontent-sin6-2.cdninstagram.com&_nc_cat=105&_nc_ohc=j5cPKdEYTLoAX_M_rrl&oh=5ad8b4ddcac39ce699a9cc210a408cdb&oe=5F7C14BD";}i:99;a:1:{s:4:"type";s:5:"image";}i:100;a:1:{s:8:"owner_id";i:18149884685;}i:101;a:1:{s:14:"owner_username";s:0:"";}i:102;a:1:{s:14:"owner_fullname";s:0:"";}i:103;a:1:{s:9:"owner_pic";s:0:"";}i:104;a:1:{s:2:"id";s:19:"2391096803004276098";}i:105;a:1:{s:10:"short_code";s:11:"CEu4d-upF2C";}i:106;a:1:{s:12:"created_time";i:1599260972;}i:107;a:1:{s:7:"caption";s:1198:"Be bold enough to live the life you imagined. 🤩🦋 ⁣
