Ingredients:
1 ½ cups (186 g) roasted cauliflower florets
¼  teaspoon curry powder 
¼  teaspoon cumin 
⅛ tsp garlic powder 
⅛ tsp onion powder 
⅛  tsp salt 
1 cup vegetable broth 
½ cup water
¼ cup lite coconut milk 
Garnish: 1 tbsp chopped cilantro 

Directions:
To roast cauliflower: Preheat oven to 450°F. Place cauliflower florets on a baking sheet and spray cauliflower with cooking spray. Bake in the center of the oven until browned and tender, about 25-30 minutes, turning the florets occasionally so they are evenly cooked.
In a small saucepan, add broth, ½ cup water and roasted cauliflower. Stir in curry powder, cumin, garlic powder, onion powder, and salt.
Bring to a boil and cook covered on low for 15 minutes. Stir in coconut milk.
Use an immersion blender (or regular blender in batches) and blend until smooth. Add additional water to get it to desired consistency. Top with cilantro.

Makes 1 Serving
3 Greens
3 Condiments
1 Healthy Fat
Serve with a Leaner option

Certified Health Coach:
Salina Watson";}i:160;a:1:{s:14:"comments_count";i:1;}i:161;a:1:{s:11:"likes_count";i:2;}i:162;a:1:{s:4:"link";s:39:"https://www.instagram.com/p/CEu4H6xBBG1";}i:163;a:1:{s:5:"image";s:239:"https://scontent-sin6-2.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.2885-15/e35/118782864_2274751226004777_2048733733421489067_n.jpg?_nc_ht=scontent-sin6-2.cdninstagram.com&_nc_cat=109&_nc_ohc=VEZf9GYsbVUAX-2fUet&oh=f0f6a5ddb2064d041f699a63f2987ec5&oe=5F7BF01F";}i:164;a:1:{s:4:"type";s:5:"image";}i:165;a:1:{s:8:"owner_id";i:402430485;}i:166;a:1:{s:14:"owner_username";s:0:"";}i:167;a:1:{s:14:"owner_fullname";s:0:"";}i:168;a:1:{s:9:"owner_pic";s:0:"";}i:169;a:1:{s:2:"id";s:19:"2391094933276015483";}i:170;a:1:{s:10:"short_code";s:11:"CEu4CxaJzt7";}i:171;a:1:{s:12:"created_time";i:1599260749;}i:172;a:1:{s:7:"caption";s:1922:"So much talk about GUT HEALTH lately. 

I am sure you’ve heard👂🏻 people say that:
✅  the gut is your second brain 🧠 (first actually)
✅ 80% of your immune system lies in your gut 

But did you know that:
✅ for every message from the brain 🧠 to the gut, there are 9 messages from the gut to the brain 🧠 
✅ you inherit your mother’s gut bacteria
✅ your intestines are 20-25 feet long
✅ you have a completely new lining of your intestines every 3-7 days 
✅ there are 100-150 times more genes 🧬 found in your microbiome than the 23,000 genes 🧬 found in your human DNA
✅ STRESS plays a major role in your gut health more then you’ll ever realize
✅ your gut keeps pathogens 🦠 out of your bloodstream. If you have a LEAKY GUT that’s where these little monsters are escaping into your bloodstream🩸, causing all kinds of health problems. LEAKY GUT is a precursor to many diseases. It is associated with lupus, type 1 diabetes, MS, fibromyalgia, arthritis, allergies, asthma, acne, obesity, IBS, Crohn’s, mental illness and even cancer
✅ your gut produces certain hormones such as thyroid hormones, hunger hormones, estrogen, serotonin, melatonin

💫 To say that your gut health should be an important PRIORITY is an understatement. 

💫 Eat only what’s good for your gut. 
“Eat plants 🌱. Mostly green. Not too much.” 
It’s hard to overeat on vegetables! 🥗
No food nourishes the body in more ways than plants. 

💫 Eliminate unhealthy, inflammation causing foods and beverages such as gluten, dairy, sugar, corn 🌽, soy, alcohol 🍺, soda 🥤 

💫 Detox your body and your digestive pathways. Detoxing is just like cleaning your home. What if you never cleaned your house? 
Our bodies store TOXINS 💀 in adipose tissue (fat) and that’s why many people are unable to loose weight. When you rid the body of toxins,the pounds will start falling off.";}i:173;a:1:{s:14:"comments_count";i:1;}i:174;a:1:{s:11:"likes_count";i:0;}i:175;a:1:{s:4:"link";s:39:"https://www.instagram.com/p/CEu4CxaJzt7";}i:176;a:1:{s:5:"image";s:239:"https://scontent-sin6-2.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.2885-15/e35/118793228_2027754707361874_8527456870140465371_n.jpg?_nc_ht=scontent-sin6-2.cdninstagram.com&_nc_cat=110&_nc_ohc=8R1R2Kxo7RsAX8lsEgi&oh=22c7522914e7879deacf68b64e230c6f&oe=5F7B6B2C";}i:177;a:1:{s:4:"type";s:5:"image";}i:178;a:1:{s:8:"owner_id";i:8546825481;}i:179;a:1:{s:14:"owner_username";s:0:"";}i:180;a:1:{s:14:"owner_fullname";s:0:"";}i:181;a:1:{s:9:"owner_pic";s:0:"";}i:182;a:1:{s:2:"id";s:19:"2391094569494419020";}i:183;a:1:{s:10:"short_code";s:11:"CEu39enFJZM";}i:184;a:1:{s:12:"created_time";i:1599260706;}i:185;a:1:{s:7:"caption";s:1204:"Instead of getting judgemental, get curious. 💞

You can only do the best you can with what you have at the time. And that goes for others as well. ✨

So we might as well get curious as to why we're feeling the way we're feeling. 👁

Ask yourself what you're feeling. 
Then ask, why you're feeling that way.
Sit with it. Own your feelings. 
And ask yourself, how you feel about having those feelings. 
Breathe into it. 🌬

Honor what comes up for you and move forward.

What can you do differently now that you know more? 🖤

I hope you find this exercise as helpful as I do! 
